{
  "name": "Holy Censure",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The means of releasing a cloud of blessed powdered silver differs, but the results remain the same. When released in the air around you a brilliant display of light is visible accompanied with a censuring hum reproducing an affect similar to <em><strong>@UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.class-and-subclass-features.Item.zH1cZzq37EJhRkK1]{Channel Divinity: Turn Undead}. </strong></em>Releasing the powder takes one action.</p><p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Any time an undead creature makes a successful saving throw to avoid the effect or end it renders the creature immune to a Holy Censure for the next 24 hours.</p><p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A turned creature must spend its turns trying to move as far away from the point of origin of the censure, and it can t willingly move to a space within 20 feet of it. It also can t take reactions. For its action, it can use only the <strong>Dodge</strong> action.</p><p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A cleric, paladin, divine soul sorcerer or ritual takes 1 hours to perform, uses a combined cost of 50 gp worth of components (powdered silver and high quality salt and/or incense) and requires the caster to expend a 1st-level spell slot.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
